                        <h4>The Starlink Revolution Continues</h4>
                        <p>Starlink Maritime has transformed yacht connectivity. The new flat high-performance dish (€2,500 + €250/month for 50GB) delivers 200+ Mbps even in challenging conditions. Installation tip: Mount as high as possible but consider a removable bracket - many Mediterranean marinas still prohibit permanent satellite installations.</p>

                        <div class="pro-tip">
                            <div class="pro-tip-header">📡 CONNECTIVITY TIP</div>
                            <p>Combine Starlink with a Pepwave MAX router (€1,500) for seamless switching between satellite, marina WiFi, and 4G. The setup seems complex but saves thousands in roaming charges annually.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <!-- Market Insights -->
                <section id="market" class="content-section">
                    <div class="section-header">
                        <span class="section-tag">MARKET WATCH</span>
                        <h2>Q4 2025 Yacht Market Analysis</h2>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="article-content">
                        <p>The yacht market is experiencing its most significant shift since 2008. Here's what smart buyers and sellers need to know:</p>

                        <div class="market-card">
                            <h4>📊 Key Market Indicators</h4>
                            <div class="market-stat">
                                <span>40-60ft Segment</span>
                                <span class="market-stat-value">↓ 12% YoY</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="market-stat">
                                <span>60-80ft Segment</span>
                                <span class="market-stat-value">↑ 3% YoY</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="market-stat">
                                <span>Average Days on Market</span>
                                <span class="market-stat-value">186 days</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="market-stat">
                                <span>Inventory Levels</span>
                                <span class="market-stat-value">↑ 34% vs 2024</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <h4>What's Driving the Shift?</h4>
                        <p>Post-pandemic buying has cooled dramatically. Interest rates have doubled since 2022, making financing expensive. The 40-60ft segment, inflated by COVID buyers, is seeing significant corrections. Quality vessels with documented maintenance still command premiums, but "project boats" are virtually unsellable.</p>

                        <h4>Hot Models to Buy Now</h4>
                        <ul style="padding-left: 20px;">
                            <li><strong>Oyster 565:</strong> Down 20% from 2023 peaks. Exceptional build quality means they'll rebound first.</li>
                            <li><strong>Princess V65:</strong> 2018-2020 models offering incredible value at €1.2-1.4M.</li>
                            <li><strong>Lagoon 52:</strong> Charter market saturation creating buying opportunities under €800k.</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h4>Models to Avoid</h4>
                        <ul style="padding-left: 20px;">
                            <li><strong>Anything Volvo IPS Gen 1 (2005-2012):</strong> Repair costs exceeding vessel values.</li>
                            <li><strong>Turkish Production 2019-2021:</strong> Quality control issues during COVID production surge.</li>
                            <li><strong>Older Ferrettis with ZF Pods:</strong> Parts availability becoming critical.</li>
                        </ul>

                        <div class="highlight-box">
                            <h4>🎯 Negotiation Strategy</h4>
                            <p>In this market, cash talks louder than ever. Sellers are accepting 15-20% below asking for quick, clean deals. Get a surveyor's report before making an offer - using specific issues as negotiation points yields better results than broad percentage demands.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>

